item.title: Project 2: Modeling, Testing, and Predicting
item.description: Mizzu Cho (mc63696) Atlantic Hurricanes I will be introducing the datatset about US Atlantic hurricanes. The dataset includes 13 different variables such as atmospheric pressure at landfall, estimated damage in millions of dollars, and deaths, for named hurricanes that made landfall in the US mainland from 1950 through to 2012 and the dataset involves 94 different hurricanes (observations). I'm going to look in whether the mean financial damages caused the hurricane differ between LA, TX, and FL.
